Project Title: Portfolio Website - Applications Development Laboratory
Course Project: Applications Development Laboratory

Project Description:
This is a simple portfolio website developed as part of the Applications Development Laboratory course. The project demonstrates the implementation of a basic web application using the Flask framework, along with HTML and CSS.

Features:
- Responsive single-page portfolio design
- Dynamic project showcase section
- Profile picture display
- Skills section
- Contact information
- Mobile-friendly navigation

Technologies Used:
- Python (Flask)
- HTML5
- CSS3
- Jinja2 Templates

Project Structure:
```
portfolio_website/
    ├── app.py               # Flask application file
    ├── static/
    │   ├── style.css        # CSS styling
    │   └── images/          # Image assets
    └── templates/
        └── index.html       # Main HTML template
```

Setup Instructions:
1. Clone the repository
2. Install Flask: `pip install flask`
3. Run the application: `python app.py`
4. Access the website at: `http://127.0.0.1:5000`

Academic Context:
This project was completed as part of the Applications Development Laboratory coursework, demonstrating practical implementation of web development concepts and framework usage.

